---
import { EnvironmentScanner } from "../../components/EnvironmentScanner";
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  name: "Proxy Geo Consistency Checker",
  url: "https://cloakbrowser.org/tools/proxy-geo-consistency-checker",
  applicationCategory: "DeveloperApplication",
  description:
    "Compare edge country, ASN, timezone, locale, and optional provider network flags against browser-visible settings."
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Proxy Geo Consistency Checker | ASN, Locale, Timezone, and Network Flags"
  description="Compare edge IP country, ASN, timezone, locale, and optional proxy/VPN intelligence with browser-visible settings for QA consistency."
  schema={schema}
>
  <section class="page-shell">
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <a href="/tools">Tools</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span>Proxy geo</span>
    </nav>
    <div class="tool-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Tool</p>
      <h1>Proxy and geography consistency checker</h1>
      <p class="subhead">
        Compare edge country, ASN, timezone, locale, and optional provider
        network flags against browser-visible settings.
      </p>
    </div>
    <EnvironmentScanner client:load />
    <article class="doc-content">
      <h2>What does proxy geo consistency mean?</h2>
      <p>
        A browser test is more repeatable when edge IP country, ASN type,
        browser timezone, language region, and optional provider intelligence
        tell the same story about the intended test location.
      </p>
      <h2>What mismatch matters most?</h2>
      <p>
        The highest-impact mismatch is an IP country that disagrees with the
        browser timezone or primary language region. For example, a US edge IP
        with `Asia/Shanghai` timezone and `zh-CN` language may invalidate a
        region-specific QA result.
      </p>
      <h2>How reliable are proxy and VPN flags?</h2>
      <p>
        Provider flags are advisory. If no IP intelligence key is configured,
        the scanner still reports Cloudflare edge geography and marks proxy/VPN
        flags unavailable instead of guessing.
      </p>
      <h2>Next step</h2>
      <p>
        Align Playwright `locale`, `timezoneId`, optional `geolocation`, and the
        network route before treating a regional browser test as production
        evidence.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
